HEADWORD: Wharfing
<hw>Wharf"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Wharfs,
collectively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Hydraul. Engin.)</fld> <def>A mode of facing sea
walls and embankments with planks driven as piles and secured by
ties.</def> <rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

